I wonder if it might not be useful to regularly publish a list of the top 20 DNS
clients or maybe a list of all the top clients which surpassed some particular
percentage of the total DNS traffic similar to the list that Paul sent out
recently.  Heaven forbid any of my systems should appear there but I think I'd
rather know about it than not know.  Seems like it might be a useful, if coarse,
diagnostic tool to whittle away at the worst offenders.  On the other hand, I
suppose that many of the worst offenders wouldn't be reading this list.

Steve Hubert
Networks and Distributed Computing, Univ. of Wash., Seattle
hubert@cac.washington.edu

